						<summary>

						<p>This is in characters of about the 9th century A.D. It is incomplete. It seems to record a gift of land for the renovation of some structure (temple ?) and worship therein by Perumpiḍugu Perundēvi, the mother of (a chief by name) Viḍēlviḍugu Viḻuppēradi-Araiśaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śāttaṉ Māṟaṉ. It is possible that this chief was related to the Muttaraiyars of Śendalai.</p>						

						</summary>
